---
import Layout from '../../../components/layout/Layout.astro';

const lang = 'en' as const;
const title = 'Ensayo Autorretrato';
---

<Layout
  lang={lang}
  title="Ensayo Autorretrato — Work"
  description="Ensayo Autorretrato (2022). Video, Espacio Continuo. The artist's hands search, scratch, destroy, and model. Maria Elvira Escallon."
>

  <article class="work-page">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="work-page__header">
        <p class="label">Work / 014</p>
        <h1>{title}</h1>
        <p class="work-page__meta">2022 &nbsp;/&nbsp; Video &nbsp;/&nbsp; Espacio Continuo</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Main gallery -->
      <div class="work-page__gallery">
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="aspect-ratio:16/9;">[ Pending: Ensayo Autorretrato — Video still, hands searching a wall ]</div>
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="aspect-ratio:16/9;">[ Pending: Ensayo Autorretrato — Video still, hands destroying Venus de Milo mask ]</div>
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="aspect-ratio:16/9;">[ Pending: Ensayo Autorretrato — Video still, arm modeled connecting to frailejon ]</div>
      </div>

      <!-- Text + Technical sheet -->
      <div class="work-page__body">
        <div class="work-page__text">

          <p class="curatorial">
            In video, the artist's hands search a wall, scratch with their nails, find a
            nail. In another sequence, her hands systematically destroy a Venus de Milo
            mask, then model an arm connecting not to a shoulder but to a frailejon — a
            plant of the Colombian paramos. The self-portrait is constructed not through
            the face but through the hands — the instruments of the artist's practice.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The title — <em>Ensayo Autorretrato</em> (Self-Portrait Essay) — signals both
            an attempt and a literary form. This is not a definitive self-portrait but an
            essay, a trial, an exploration. The video unfolds as a series of gestures that
            reveal the artist's relationship to materials, surfaces, and the act of making
            itself. To scratch, to find, to destroy, to model — these are the verbs of
            Escallon's practice, distilled into their most elemental form.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The destruction of the Venus de Milo mask — an icon of classical Western beauty —
            and the subsequent modeling of an arm that connects to a frailejon enact a
            symbolic displacement: from European canonical beauty to Colombian highland
            ecology, from the idealized human form to the hybrid human-vegetal body. The
            frailejon, a plant endemic to the paramos of the Andes, becomes a surrogate for
            the shoulder, suggesting that the artist's body extends into and is completed
            by the landscape she inhabits.
          </p>

          <h3 style="margin-top: var(--s4);">CONTEXT</h3>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            Presented at Espacio Continuo in 2022, <em>Ensayo Autorretrato</em> is one of
            Escallon's most explicitly personal works, yet it avoids conventional
            self-portraiture entirely. The face never appears; identity is conveyed through
            action rather than image. The work connects to <em>Encuentros con Seres
            Notables</em> (also 2022) in its exploration of human-vegetal kinship, and
            to the broader arc of Escallon's practice in its engagement with destruction
            as a creative act.
          </p>
        </div>

        <aside class="work-page__ficha">
          <h4>TECHNICAL SHEET</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            <strong>Ensayo Autorretrato</strong><br>
            2022<br><br>
            Video.<br><br>
            Espacio Continuo
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">EXHIBITIONS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            Espacio Continuo, 2022
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">HOW TO CITE</h4>
          <div class="ficha" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">
            Escallon, M.E. (2022). <em>Ensayo Autorretrato</em>.
            Video. Available at:
            mariaelviraescallon.com/en/works/ensayo-autorretrato/
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>

</Layout>

<style>
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    }
</style>
